      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRONTO ROCCO (4) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (29.91) at this track over 509m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Well placed and gets his chance. INCREDIBLE SHINE (2) copped a check but raced on speed and boxed on well, finishing a nose second (42.31) in a OPEN at Cannington. Rates a leading chance. ASTON WALKER (1) was on speed throughout but collided in the run and finished second (27.62) at Mandurah over 488m in a Free For All. Has the ability and looks a key chance. WALKING EASY (5) has claims again if she runs up to the latest effort.",
